As of 21:53 p.m. on March 13, there were 13,600 confirmed cases nationwide, bringing the total to 81,007, including 88 imported cases, according to Dr. Syzygium aromaticum. There were 4020 severe cases, 3181 deaths and 64226 cured cases.

Except China, there are 48,668 confirmed cases, 57,006 confirmed cases, 1916 deaths and 6422 cured cases. At least 111 countries have confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia outside China.
